 Ficus deltoidea varieties on glycation-induced protein oxidation were done by measuring the inhibition of protein carbonyl formation and thiol groups. 
  Figure 2 shows that the inhibition of protein carbonyl formation was significantly increased after 28 days of incubation. Quercetin is a positive control and showed a 3.04-fold of inhibition (
 p < 0.001) at a concentration of 0.50â€‰mg/mL. FDT was found to possess the highest fold of inhibition at 1.76 (
